page.title: 08A52 Main Road
page.content: The results of a survey on the A52 going West, from 2.00.p.m. until 2.30.p.m. There were 105 cars, 1 motor bike, 2 caravans, 32 lorries, 33 vans, and two coaches. A similar survey going East from 3.15.p.m. until 3.45.p.m. There were 135 cars, 2 motor bikes, 3 caravans, 27 lorries, 7 coaches and 12 vans. There is a garage and a cafe at Sedgebrook. Petrol at the garage costs 43.5p per litre of 4 star. The cafe is very cheap and you can buy cottage pie, roast potatoes and gravy for Â£1.40. Apple pie and custard costs 40p. and tea is included. Behind the garage there is a small factory producing hydraulic equipment for the home and export markets.
